post_text:
Recent federal law to support COVID-19 relief created the Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) program as an important nutritional resource to families who lost access to free or reduced-price school meals as schools across Colorado closed in response to COVID-19. P-EBT provides households with an EBT card funded with the value of the free school breakfast and lunch reimbursement rates for the days that schools have been closed in March, April, and May, which equals $5.70 per day. Those funds can then be spent on eligible food items at many local and online retail stores. For a list of eligible items, visit the USDA Food and Nutrition Service website. https://www.fns.usda.gov/snap/eligible-food-items
Families may apply for P-EBT cards online at https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdhs/p-ebt

post_text:
Weldon Valley School District 2020 Senior Graduation

We wanted to update everyone with graduation finally upon us! We will be celebrating our seniors outdoors this Saturday starting at 10:00 AM. We will have our stage located North of the ag shop. We will have reserved seating for our seniors’ guests. All other guests that want to celebrate the accomplishments of our seniors are asked to bring lawn chairs and maintain a social distance of six feet from the other guests. We are requiring no contact with our seniors, no hugging, shaking hands, etc. to comply with the mandates from the health department. Masks are suggested but not mandatory due to being outside. We ask that you do not attend if you have underlying health concerns, are not feeling well, or running a fever.

We will have the ceremony streamed live on our school Facebook page, Weldon Valley School District, for those unable to attend. Please share this information with those that might be interested.

If you have any questions, please let us know. See you Saturday!

Sincerely,

Ben Bauman
